# Data Map Configuration Example
# Format: source|dest|ignore_patterns|mode
#
# source: Full path to source directory
# dest: Subdirectory name under backup destination
# ignore_patterns: Comma-separated gitignore-style patterns (optional, use empty for none)
# mode: incremental (default) or mirror
#
# Incremental Mode: Only backup files that have changed since the last backup
# Mirror Mode: Exact mirror of source (adds --delete to remove extra files)
#
# This configuration is used bidirectionally:
# - Backup: source → dest (original location → backup subdirectory)
# - Restore: dest → source (backup subdirectory → original location)

# Example entries:

# User home directory (excluding downloads and caches)
/home/username|home_username|Downloads/,downloads/,.cache/,*.tmp,*.log|incremental

# Important documents folder
/home/username/Documents|documents||incremental

# Media collection (exclude temporary files)
/home/username/Media|media|*.tmp,*.partial|incremental

# Projects directory (excluding build artifacts)
/home/username/Projects|projects|node_modules/,target/,build/,dist/,.git/|incremental

# System configuration files
/etc|system_config|shadow,shadow-,gshadow,gshadow-,passwd-,group-|incremental

# Website/project directory (exact mirror)
/var/www|www|*.log,tmp/|mirror